Service quality analysis from Yelp reviews

Manuel Walser
22th October 2015

Links

  • Coursera: https://www.coursera.org/course/dsscapstone
  • Yelp: http://www.yelp.com/dataset_challenge
  • Code: https://bitbucket.org/higgser/yelpchallenge

Motivation

  • Coursera capstone project and 6th Yelp Challange 2015
  • Learn about text and sentiment analysis methods
  • Extract service quality from reviews
  • Compare cultural differences between cities and users
  • Verify hypothesis about importance of service quality

Dataset

  • 20'000 restaurants in 10 cities and 3 countries
  • 990'000 restaurants reviews from 220'000 users
  • 510'000 english sentences about service quality
  • Residence of users missing

Methods

  • K-means to cluster business in regions
  • Language detection with n-grams (textcat)
  • Sentence detector (OpenNLP)
  • Polarity rating with sentiment dictionary (Qdap)
  • Residence predictor for 63'000 users

Challanges and Outlook

  • Performance of R
  • German sentiment analysis
  • Autocorrection of typos
  • Differentation between service in general and staff
